## Pay-Per-Click Advertising (PPC)

Corporate PPC campaigns only support and target domestic audiences. There are no specific guidelines for international campaigns; Distributors are free to create their own PPC campaigns.

---

## Search Engine Optimization (SEO)

### Meta Data

Geo Group will translate all Meta data that are live on the US site during the initial-site translation. Any new pages or product pages will be created with English Meta data only and it will be the responsibility of the Distributor to properly translate. _See appendix for additional information on Meta data._

### Redirects

It is assumed that each Distributor will work directly with HI to align on needed 301 or 302 redirects. Redirects should be set up to create a nearly 1:1 relationship between old pages and new relevant pages. 

### Sitemap

Each Distributor site will have its own sitemap. _See appendix for additional information on how to find your sitemap._

### Google Search Counsel

HI will create a Google Search Counsel profile for each Distributor. This allows for high-level search performance monitoring and the submission of new sitemaps or index requests. 

### Adobe Analytics

To access the real-time reporting dashboard, visit [https://my.omniture.com/login/](https://my.omniture.com/login/)

Use your team-shared credentials to access the account (each partner group will receive a unique login). Company name should be entered as: subzero-wolf.

## SEO Within Sitecore

![](data:image/*;base64,)

When your website launched, a number of pages within your site will already have Meta data implemented, and we continually add and modify each week. In addition, you too can add and modify your SEO Meta Data as needed. 

Navigate to the page within Sitecore that you would like to update and click the SEO Information section within that page. You will notice 4 fields: 

- SEO Title
- Meta Keywords
- Tracking Scripts  _ignore!_
